					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Actually Akumajou Densetsu/VRC6 can easily fit onto a CPLD, it requires about 120 macrocells. VRC7 can probably too, I haven't tried. All games with similar bankswitching schemes have similar requirements.
<br />
<br />Also both protection against writing PRG and CHR ROM is very simple, all it requires is two register bits and two OR gates to lock the /WR pins on the RAM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

